in real project we have over thousands commits on each project!
so we need filter them!

git log --oneline -3                        //show just pre 3 commits!

git log --oneline --author="Cenna"          //filter commits by author name

git log --oneline --after="yesterday"       //we can use "before" instead after
git log --oneline --after="2020-08-17"
git log --oneline --after="one week ago"
git log --oneline --after="two days ago"

git log --oneline 9b6ebfd..91f7d40          //find all commits between two commits

git log --oneline toc.txt                   //find all commits that modify or change "toc.txt" file

git log --oneline --grep="GUI"              //search commit by commit message! (it's case sensitive)
Note: he find some commit
      (24e86ee Add command line and GUI tools to the objectives.)
      we can use show command to see that commit:
      "git show 24e86ee"



git log --oneline -S"OBJECTIVES"           //search commits by content
we can use show command to see             //it will find all commits that add/remove line
the commits he find!                       //that contain "OBJECTIVES" word
or we can use "patch" directly to see
what has changed:
git log --oneline -S"OBJECTIVES" --patch


